{
  "texts": [
    "Then, an output signal y distil is generated for x distil using the model with its previous, frozen, parameter set θ 1:s-1 as well as its current parameter set θ 1:s, which we denote by ŷdistil.",
    "As the goal is for the new outputs to be consistent with the old outputs, we compute loss L distil, which is combined with the fitting loss L f it,L total = L f it + λL distil,where λ balances plasticity and stability.",
    "This approach requires no access to previous data, only the prior model parameters, making it highly memory-efficient.",
    "We evaluated the proposed approach on the training set of the Automated Cardiac Diagnosis Challenge (ACDC) challenge [15], which contains 3D+t MRI scans of 100 patients.",
    "Each scan consists of a sequence of 3D frames covering one complete cardiac cycle."
  ]
}